Sequence Information.Peptide Name: CFPS_AMP_16 (cell-free protein synthesis-AMP 16, Lys-rich, AI predicted AMPs, UCLL1)
Sequence Information.Source: AI predicted, machine learning prediction of known protein sequences

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (39.29%) toAMP_5. K: 36%; F: 15%.Activity: active against E. coli (MIC 6.3 uM), B. subtilis (MIC 0.8 uM), A. baumannii clinical strain (MIC 1.6 uM), Enterobacter spp. (MIC >25 uM), K. pneumoniae DSM 30104 (MIC 2.4 uM), P. aeruginosa DSM 1117 (MIC 12.5 uM), S. aureus DSM 11729 MRSA (MIC 25 uM), E. faecium (MIC 1.6 uM), Y. pestis EV76 (MIC 4.2 uM), B. anthracis Sterne (MIC 4.2 uM), and S-pneumoniae D39 (MIC >25 uM).Toxicity: Human RBC: HC50 180.2 uM, not hemo.lytic.Resistance development:no:bacteria:E. coli: E. coli did not develop resistance to the peptide after 21 passages.
Literature Information.Author: Pandi A, Adam D, Zare A, Trinh VT, Schaefer SL, Burt M, Klabunde B, Bobkova E, Kushwaha M, Foroughijabbari Y, Braun P, Spahn C, Preußer C, Pogge von Strandmann E, Bode HB, von Buttlar H, Bertrams W, Jung AL, Abendroth F, Schmeck B, Hummer G, Vázquez O, Erb TJ. 2023
